With all the investments made in analytics, it’s time to stop buying into partial solutions that overpromise and underdeliver. It’s time to invest in answers. Only Icloudsys leverages all of the data, all of the time, so that customers can analyze anything, deploy anywhere, and deliver analytics that matter most to them. And we do it at scale, on-premises, in the Cloud, or anywhere in between.
We call this Pervasive Data Intelligence. It’s the answer to the complexity, cost, and inadequacy of today’s analytics. And it’s the way Icloudsys transforms how businesses work and people live through the power of data throughout the world. Join us and help create the era of Pervasive Data Intelligence.
Job Specification
Successful candidates will –
Be a credible thought leader in discussion on public/hybrid cloud solutions with customers and analysts;
Work collaboratively with Solution Architects and Solution Engineers to support customer and account teams in migrating to, and developing new analytic solutions on public cloud environments
Engage with senior business leaders to understand and shape their goals and objectives and their corresponding information needs and analytic requirements;
Contribute to the financial objectives of Teradata account teams through business development, demand creation and billable consulting activities.
Participate in the development and curation of architecture assets that improve the performance and effectiveness of the Teradata account and consulting teams;
Provide thought leadership and share their hard-won skills and experience with peers and colleagues throughout the organization.
Candidate Profile
Successful candidates must –
Be passionate and enthusiastic about data, analytics and Teradata;
Have at least 5+ years hands-on experience in architecting, designing, delivering or optimizing Data Warehouse and/or Data Lake solutions;
Have at least one year’s recent hands-on experience with architecting and delivering Cloud solutions in the context of Data & Analytic Ecosystem (BI, DWH and Big Data) in the public cloud arena
Be a clear, confident and persuasive communicator, with excellent presentation skills and with the ability to structure a coherent, logical argument and the confidence to defend assumptions, projections and recommendations;
Demonstrate a keen interest and understanding of developments in the data and analytic technology marketplace and the trends that are driving the adoption of new analytic technologies;
Develop and mentor colleagues and peers throughout the GDC organization;
Help and provide technical direction to GDC projects on cloud related matters.
Be proficient in the use of both written and spoken business English;
Possess strong analytical and problem-solving skills;
Demonstrate excellent organizational and people skills.
Successful candidates will preferably –
Have a background in technology consulting and relevant pre-sales experience;
Have broad technical knowledge of the public cloud offerings of key providers such as AWS, Azure and Google and demonstrated capability to architect and design custom public / hybrid cloud solutions that meet the business and security needs of the customer;
AWS/Azure or Google Cloud Certification as a Solution Architect Associate/Professional or deemed to have equivalent experience;
Expert level knowledge and working experience of a variety of cloud products and services (e.g. Amazon EC2, Amazon S3, Amazon DynamoDB, Amazon Redshift, Amazon CloudFront, Amazon EMR and/or Azure equivalent);
Significant working knowledge or hands-on experience with cloud SDK and CLI Tools, experience in building / deploying complex infrastructure, and experience in Network design and technical implementation;
Proven hands-on cloud migration solution design / delivery experience;
Ability to effectively address data security concepts in public cloud as it relates to customer needs including an in depth understanding of Federated Security / Single Sign On, and IAM;
Be familiar with SQL and at least one other relevant analytic programming language;
Have a degree level qualification in Computer Science, Software Engineering or a related discipline.
